messages.body: $JBHT  way oversold going into their busiest  season ever.

$JBHT  $YRC $USX $WERN

If I ever saw a ridiculous valuation hit based on an "earnings miss," this JBHT drop is amongst the dumbest...

Underlying the quarter is a recovering economy, retail sales and the need for transport services... and here is the only part of the press release that needs my attention:

"Volumes in the quarter were heavily constrained by rail congestion and service issues stemming from a large and sudden increase in demand and intermittent labor challenges in both the rail and truck networks."

JBHT is a well run company, and they will make the logistics adjustments they need to handle the "LARGE AND SUDDEN INCREASE IN DEMAND" -- with a certain increase in revnues, Gross margin, operating income, EBITDA and FCF...  

The stock is going higher after the quant fheads get done trying to tool on the clueless... those shorting down here will be torched.

$XPO $USAK
